    "description": "`pytest-fail-slow` is a pytest plugin for making tests fail that take too long to run.  It adds a `--fail-slow DURATION` command-line option to pytest that causes any & all otherwise-passing tests that run for longer than the given duration to be marked as failures, and it adds a `@pytest.mark.fail_slow(DURATION)` marker for making an individual test fail if it runs for longer than the given duration.  If `--fail-slow` is given and a test has the `@fail_slow()` marker, the duration given by the marker takes precedence for that test.",
